This press briefing discusses several topics, including immigration, the Congressional Review Act, regulatory burden, and healthcare. Marc Short, Director of Legislative Affairs, provides an update on the Congressional Review Act and explains how the administration is working to roll back regulations. He highlights the impact of regulations on the economy and the efforts to reduce the regulatory burden. Short also mentions the ongoing discussions on healthcare reform and the administration's commitment to tax reform. He emphasizes the importance of the Congressional Review Act in achieving these goals and addresses concerns about the potential consequences of using the CRA extensively.